#   GET-026: bare `be get` = default GET + resulting-state banner

Make bare `be get` (no URI) the **default GET** — update the wt to the
current branch tip (FF when the wt lags) — instead of printing a raw
branches/remotes summary. Route its report through the shared ROWS
state banner ([BE-005]) whose uri is the *resulting state*:
`?<branch>#<hashlet>` for the main project, `<path>#<hashlet>` for a
submodule. The branch/remote overview moves to [STATUS-001].

##  Input

### Context
 -  `be` (no verb) → `BEDefault` → `sniff` no-verb = file **status**; the
    branch/remote overview is NOT shown there.
 -  Bare `be get` wrongly calls `SNIFFGetSummary` (`SNIFF.exe.c:1127`; raw
    `fprintf`, `GET.c:1697`) — its ONLY caller; spec `GET.mkd:23` "no-op".
 -  `be get ?` reaches `SNIFFGet` (`GET.c:1572`) but opens ROWS with
    `empty_uri` + KEYED → flat rows, no banner ([BE-005] core fixes this).

### Goals
 -  Bare `be get` resolves the cur branch (`SNIFFAtBaseline`, trunk if
    empty) and runs the checkout/update path; FF the wt when lagging.
 -  `SNIFFGet` opens ROWS with `uri = ?<branch>#<hashlet>` (main) /
    `<path>#<hashlet>` (sub), `verb=get`, `ts=now` — the resolved target
    sha gives the 8-hex hashlet (`be head`/`log` style).
 -  Spec `GET.mkd:23` updated; submodule banner `<path>#<hashlet>` relays
    via `HUNKu8sRelay` unchanged.

### Constraints
 -  Depends on the [BE-005] ROWS banner-once core; no per-site banner.
 -  `sniff/` only; no `abc/` ([[abc-changes-need-review]]).

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Build the banner uri from `(branch|subpath, target-sha→8hex)` — the
    sha is the checkout target, already known in `SNIFFGet`.
 -  Drop the `SNIFFGetSummary` call from get; the function's body is
    rehomed by [STATUS-001], not deleted yet.

